&lt;p&gt;Hello, Everyone:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;HK GTUG is going to have a second event in City University in Kowloon. Google China DevRel Technical Program Manager and China Country Lead Bill Luan (whom many of you have already met during our first event in March), will present HTML5, Google TV and Google map API.We welcome HK GTUG, HKITF, WTIA and HKWDC members to join. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a great opportunity to learn the concepts of these key technologies. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Feel free to forward this message to your friends who are interested!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Details as follow:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Date (Time): 29/06/2010 (14:00-17:00)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Venue: LT-13 City University of Hong Kong&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Estimated no. of Participants: 120&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Agenda:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1:45-2:00 – Registration&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;2:00-2:45 – HTML5 (Bill)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;2:45-3:15 – Google TV (Bill)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;3:15-3:30 - Break&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;3:30-4:00 – Google Map API (Bill)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;4:00-4:30 – Commercial use case on Google Technology&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;4:30-17:00 - Questionnaire&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Thank you HKITF, WTIA and HKWDC to promote this event to their members and City University sponsor the room. Apologize for this short notice, we will work with Google China's DevRel team to organize more HK GTUG events in the coming month.  So event if you can not go to this event at this time, be rest assured that we will have more opportunities to learn and exchange with Googlers in the near future.&lt;/p&gt;
